situation.situation: A trough, followed by strong southwesterlies, moves across the country today and early Sunday. On Monday a low moves on to northern New Zealand from the north Tasman Sea, then stalls and weakens over northern New Zealand on Tuesday while a ridge develops over the South Island. On Wednesday the low remains slow moving over the far north, the ridge lies over central New Zealand and southwesterlies affect the far south.
